Highway robbery!  I am retired nurse of 20+ years. Literally a 5 minute video conference with a doctor in between his regularly scheduled patients was $150! That translates to $1800/hour!    The app does not mention additional charges from the office. Only the $49/per call charge, all charges listed upfront. Even the doctor I spoke with stated it was a 1-time charge of $49 only, I double checked with him before moving on to my problem (an infection in which I needed antibiotics.  I had already been to my regular doctor and finished one course of antibiotics. A 2nd course was needed but my doc was on vacation.)  Now the office in question is billing me for an additional $101 stating that is their normal charge for a 5 minute consultation (150 - 49 = 101).  This is not an acceptable nor economical use of telemedicine.  Will never use Now Clinic nor Southwest Medical (Las Vegas, NV) again.  Husband is a 30 year truck driver. We travel often due to the nature of his work.  Making it home for scheduled doctor's visits can be difficult.  There is a huge need for affordable, reasonable, easy to use telemedicine services in this highly mobile, remote working, age we live in today.
